This paper proposes a novel convolutional neural network (CNN) for end-to-end automatic target recognition (ATR) from synthetic aperture radar (SAR) imagery. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on deep learning, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new CNN architecture, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on SAR imagery and target recognition could also place it in the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
